==Generalizations==

The concept of in composition algebras does share the usual properties of a norm.

A composition algebra formula_203 consists of an algebra over a field formula_204 an involution formula_205 and a quadratic form formula_206 which is called the &quot;norm&quot;. In several cases formula_207 is an isotropic quadratic form so that formula_208 has at least one null vector, contrary to the separation of points required for the usual norm discussed in this article.

An or a is a seminorm formula_4 that also satisfies formula_210

